{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779181855854,"sessionID":"ses_1c07feae8ffe1KM7G6zC8Y3nGT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_JHofKIrgDcQgx7FZP8DM6400","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Domain Research — NestFind\n2: \n3: **Generated:** 2026-05-19\n4: **Source:** Phase 2.5 — Domain & Reference Research\n5: **Purpose:** Identify standard UI patterns and essential sections from top rental property listing platforms before Design Guide generation.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Industry\n10: \n11: **Domain:** Real Estate / Rental Property Listings\n12: \n13: NestFind operates in the digital rental marketplace vertical — a subset of PropTech (Property Technology) focused exclusively on long-term residential rentals (as opposed to short-term/vacation rentals or property sales). The platform connects renters with available properties through search, discovery, detail views, favorites, and inquiry submission.\n14: \n15: **Market Context:**\n16: - The US online rental market is dominated by Zillow Rentals, Apartments.com, and Realtor.com Rentals\n17: - Mobile-first search behavior is standard — renters browse on mobile, apply on desktop\n18: - Key differentiator for newer entrants: streamlined UX, fewer ads, verified listings, built-in application/inquiry flows\n19: - Map-based search and card-based results are industry-standard UI patterns\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Competitors\n24: \n25: ### Competitor 1: Zillow Rentals (zillow.com/rentals)\n26: \n27: **Type:** Full rental marketplace (listings + application management)\n28: **USP:** Largest inventory, end-to-end renter lifecycle (search → apply → pay rent)\n29: \n30: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n31: - Hero section with large search bar (location input + submit) and tagline \"Zillions of apartments. Ready when you are.\"\n32: - Feature highlight cards: \"A variety of filters and a large network of rentals\", \"A central Renter Hub\", \"1 fee, 1 form for 30 days\"\n33: - \"Looking for something specific?\" section with quick-filter chips: Pet-friendly, Apartments, Rentals with parking\n34: - \"Apply without all the paperwork\" section explaining the application process\n35: - \"Paying rent online with Zillow is easy\" — ancillary service promotion\n36: - Budget calculator CTA\n37: - Blog/resources section: \"Let's find what you're looking for\" with renter guide, budget tool, payment setup\n38: - Mobile app download promotion\n39: - Standard footer with About, News, Research, Careers, Help, Legal\n40: \n41: **Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n42: - Split view: Map on left/right (toggleable), card list on opposite side\n43: - Filter panel: Price range (min-max), Beds & Baths (min dropdowns), Property Type (multiselect), + More Filters\n44: - \"Save search\" button prominently placed\n45: - Property cards: Thumbnail image, price (prominent, large font), address (street + city/state), bed/bath counts, square footage, \"Contact\" or \"Apply\" CTA\n46: - Cards show heart/favorite icon for saved properties\n47: - Empty state: \"We could not find any matching results\" with search tips (widen area, reduce filters)\n48: - Pagination OR infinite scroll\n49: \n50: **Detail Page Patterns:**\n51: - Photo gallery with arrow navigation (carousel or grid)\n52: - Price, address, key stats (beds, baths, sqft) in header\n53: - Tabs/sections: Overview, Facts & Features, Schools, Nearby\n54: - Description (free text)\n55: - Amenities list with icons\n56: - Google Map embed with pin\n57: - Sidebar: Request Tour / Apply / Contact buttons\n58: - Favorite toggle (heart icon)\n59: \n60: **Renter Hub (Dashboard):**\n61: - Sidebar nav: Search, Saved Searches, Favorites, Messages, Applications, Payments\n62: - Central dashboard showing recent activity, application statuses\n63: - \"Your search\" section: active searches with new listing counts\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ### Competitor 2: Apartments.com\n68: \n69: **Type:** Rental aggregator with heavy advertising model\n70: **USP:** Massive inventory, neighborhood guides, 3D tours\n71: \n72: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n73: - Prominent search bar with city/address input\n74: - \"Popular Searches\" links to major cities\n75: - Featured neighborhoods/properties\n76: - Rental tools: Rent calculator, moving center, neighborhood guides\n77: - \"Find Apartments by State\" directory grid\n78: \n79: **Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n80: - Filter-heavy sidebar: Price, Beds, Baths, Property Type, Amenities (checkboxes), Pet Policy, Transit Score, Rating\n81: - Sort options: Best Match, Price (Low to High), Price (High to Low), Most Recent\n82: - Property cards: Photo, price, address, bed/bath, sqft, \"Available Now\" badge, rating stars\n83: - Map/list toggle view\n84: - \"Save\" button per card\n85: \n86: **Detail Page Patterns:**\n87: - Large photo gallery with thumbnail strip\n88: - Floor plan section (image uploads)\n89: - Amenities grid with checkmarks\n90: - Map with nearby points of interest (transit, restaurants, schools)\n91: - Contact sidebar: Phone, Email, Schedule Tour, Apply Online\n92: - Price history and availability timeline\n93: \n94: **Admin/Manager Dashboard (Apartments.com Manager):**\n95: - Property portfolio overview\n96: - Listing performance stats (views, leads, inquiries)\n97: - Lead/inquiry inbox with statuses (New, Contacted, Tour Scheduled)\n98: - Property listing editor (photos, description, pricing, availability)\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ### Competitor 3: Airbnb (airbnb.com)\n103: \n104: **Type:** Short-term rental marketplace\n105: **USP:** Best-in-class UX, immersive design, host/guest marketplace\n106: \n107: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n108: - Category bar (horizontal scroll chips): Rooms, Mansions, Amazing pools, Cabins, etc.\n109: - Card grid with large photos, location name, distance, dates, price per night\n110: - Each card: Carousel of photos, heart (wishlist) button, location, host type, rating, price\n111: - Search: \"Where\", \"Check in / Check out\" (date picker), \"Who\" (guests selector)\n112: - \"Inspiration for your next trip\" sections (themed, curated)\n113: \n114: **Detail Page Patterns:**\n115: - Full-width immersive photo gallery with \"Show all photos\" button\n116: - Title, rating, location, host info in header\n117: - Sectioned below: Description, What this place offers (amenities with icons), Where you'll sleep (bedroom breakdown), Map, Host info, Things to know (house rules)\n118: - Right sidebar: Price, date picker, guest selector, \"Reserve\" CTA, total calculation\n119: - Wishlist/save functionality (heart icon)\n120: \n121: **Key Design Lessons:**\n122: - Immersive, photo-first design\n123: - Card carousels on search results pages\n124: - Sectioned, scannable detail pages\n125: - Sticky booking/reserve sidebar (or bottom bar on mobile)\n126: - Trust-building elements: host profiles, reviews, verified badges\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ### Competitor 4: Rentable (rentable.co)\n131: \n132: **Type:** Rental marketplace with verified listings focus\n133: **USP:** Human-verified listings, budget calculator, mobile-first\n134: \n135: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n136: - Hero: \"Every Apartment Near You, In One Place\" + city search input\n137: - Listing count prominently displayed: \"Browse 10,377,478 apartments\"\n138: - Grid of popular cities with images\n139: - Grid of \"Apartments for Rent Near College Campuses\"\n140: - Testimonials and press mentions (Curbed, NBC Today)\n141: - Mobile app promotion with ratings (4.7 Apple, 3.6 Google Play)\n142: - Rent affordability calculator CTA\n143: - \"Real Apartments, Verified by Real People\" trust section\n144: - \"What is Rentable?\" about section\n145: - \"Advertising a Property?\" partner CTA\n146: - Trusted by: Forbes, MarketWatch, CNBC, Realtor.com, Washington Post logos\n147: \n148: **Key Design Lessons:**\n149: - Social proof sections (press mentions, trust logos, ratings)\n150: - City/campus browse grids for SEO and discovery\n151: - Clear value proposition: \"Every Apartment Near You, In One Place\"\n152: - Strong mobile-first design\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ### Competitor 5: HotPads (hotpads.com)\n157: \n158: **Type:** Map-centric rental search (owned by Zillow Group)\n159: **USP:** Map-first browsing experience with polygon search\n160: \n161: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n162: - Minimal: search + city links\n163: - No landing \"page\" — immediately drops users into map search\n164: \n165: **Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n166: - Full-screen map as primary interface\n167: - Listing cards overlay on top of map\n168: - Polygon search (draw area on map)\n169: - Filter bar: Price, Beds, Property Type, More\n170: - Color-coded map pins by price tier\n171: - \"My HotPads\" section: Saved searches, saved listings\n172: \n173: **Key Design Lessons:**\n174: - Map as the primary interface (alternative to card-first approach)\n175: - Minimal design with high information density on map\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## Reference UI Patterns\n180: \n181: ### Pattern 1: Property Search Card\n182: \n183: **Present in 100% of competitors.** The standard rental property card contains:\n184: \n185: | Element | Typical Size/Position | Prevalence |\n186: |---------|----------------------|------------|\n187: | Primary photo (thumbnail) | Top, ~280-340px width, 16:9 or 4:3 ratio | 100% |\n188: | Price | Large, bold, top-right or bottom-left of photo | 100% |\n189: | Address/Location | Below photo, primary text | 100% |\n190: | Bed/Bath Count | Below photo, secondary text (e.g., \"2 bd | 1 ba\") | 100% |\n191: | Square Footage | Below photo, secondary text | 80% |\n192: | Property Type Badge | On photo overlay (e.g., \"Apartment\", \"Condo\") | 60% |\n193: | Favorite/Heart Toggle | Top-right corner of card or photo | 80% |\n194: | \"New\" or \"Available Now\" Badge | On photo overlay | 50% |\n195: | Rating Stars | Below photo (if reviews available) | 30% |\n196: | Photo Count | On photo (e.g., \"1/12\" or \"📷 12\") | 70% |\n197: | \"Contact\" / \"Apply\" CTA | Bottom of card or hover overlay | 60% |\n198: \n199: ### Pattern 2: Search Filter Panel\n200: \n201: **Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard filter hierarchy:\n202: \n203: 1. **Location** (text input, autocomplete) — always first\n204: 2. **Price Range** (min-max sliders or inputs) — always present\n205: 3. **Bedrooms** (dropdown: Studio, 1+, 2+, 3+, 4+) — always present\n206: 4. **Property Type** (checkboxes: Apartment, House, Condo, Townhouse, Studio) — always present\n207: 5. **Bathrooms** (dropdown: 1+, 1.5+, 2+, 3+) — present in ~80%\n208: 6. **Amenities** (checkboxes: In-unit laundry, Parking, Pet-friendly, AC, Gym, Pool, etc.) — present in ~90%\n209: 7. **Square Footage** (range) — present in ~50%\n210: 8. **Move-in Date** (date picker) — present in ~30%\n211: 9. **Sort** (Best Match, Price Low/High, Newest, Rating) — always present\n212: 10. **\"Save Search\"** button — present in ~70%\n213: \n214: ### Pattern 3: Photo Gallery (Detail Page)\n215: \n216: **Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard patterns:\n217: \n218: - **Hero Gallery:** Large featured image with left/right arrows for navigation\n219: - **Thumbnail Strip:** Row of smaller thumbnails below hero for quick selection\n220: - **\"View All Photos\" Button:** Opens full-screen lightbox gallery\n221: - **Photo Count Badge:** e.g., \"1/12\" or \"Show all 12 photos\"\n222: - **Floor Plan Section:** Separate from photo gallery, often with interactive zoom\n223: - **Virtual Tour / 3D Tour Link:** Increasingly common (Apartments.com, Zillow)\n224: \n225: ### Pattern 4: Map Integration\n226: \n227: **Present in 95% of competitors.**\n228: \n229: - **Embedded Map (Detail Page):** Google Maps iframe with property pin marker; often shows nearby points of interest (transit, schools, restaurants)\n230: - **Map/Split View (Search Page):** Left panel = card list, right panel = full map; pins update as map pans; drawn area search\n231: - **Map Pin Design:** Custom marker with price overlay (Zillow), color-coded by price tier (HotPads)\n232: \n233: ### Pattern 5: Favorites / Saved Properties\n234: \n235: **Present in 90% of competitors.**\n236: \n237: - Heart icon toggle on property cards and detail page header\n238: - \"Saved\" or \"Favorites\" page: grid/list of favorited properties\n239: - Requires authentication (guest users prompted to sign in)\n240: - Often named \"Saved Homes,\" \"Favorites,\" or \"Saved Properties\"\n241: - May show count badge in navigation (Zillow: \"Favorites (3)\")\n242: \n243: ### Pattern 6: Inquiry / Contact Form\n244: \n245: **Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard fields: Name, Email, Phone (optional), Message. Submitted to property manager. Typically a modal or sidebar form.\n246: \n247: ### Pattern 7: Admin Dashboard (Property Management)\n248: \n249: **Based on Behance/Dribbble research of property management dashboard designs (~20 analyzed projects):**\n250: \n251: Standard dashboard elements:\n252: - **Sidebar Navigation:** Dashboard, Properties, Inquiries/Messages, Users, Settings, Reports\n253: - **Top Bar:** Search, Notifications bell, User avatar + dropdown\n254: - **Overview Stats Cards:** Total Properties, Active Listings, Total Inquiries, Pending Responses, Total Users — displayed as 4-6 metric cards with icon, value, label, trend indicator\n255: - **Recent Activity Feed:** Timeline of recent inquiries, new user registrations, listing changes\n256: - **Properties Table:** Columns: Photo (40px thumb), Title, Type, Price, Status (Active/Archived/Draft), Bed/Bath, Date Added, Actions (Edit, Delete, View). With search, filter, sort, pagination.\n257: - **Inquiry Table:** Columns: Name, Email, Property, Date, Status (New/Read/Responded), Actions (View, Reply, Mark Read)\n258: - **Users Table:** Renter list with Name, Email, Join Date, Status (Active/Suspended), Actions\n259: - **Property Editor:** Form with sections: Basic Info, Location/Address, Pricing, Details (beds, baths, sqft, type), Amenities (checkboxes grouped by category), Photos (multi-upload with drag-drop, reorder, preview), Floor Plan upload. Submit/Cancel buttons.\n260: - **Inquiry Detail/Response View:** Original inquiry message + reply textarea + Mark as Read/Responded status change + Send Reply button\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Page-type Conventions\n265: \n266: ### Landing Page\n267: \n268: **Standard Sections (present in 80%+ of competitors):**\n269: \n270: | # | Section | Purpose | Prevalence | NestFind Applicability |\n271: |---|---------|---------|------------|------------------------|\n272: | 1 | **Navigation Bar** | Logo, nav links, Sign In / Join CTAs | 100% | Required |\n273: | 2 | **Hero + Search** | Primary search input (city/address) + value prop tagline + CTA | 100% | Required — NestFind's primary entry point |\n274: | 3 | **Popular Cities / Quick Links** | Grid of city images linking to pre-filtered searches | 80% | Recommended for SEO and discovery |\n275: | 4 | **How It Works** | 3-step diagram explaining search → find → apply | 70% | Recommended for first-time users |\n276: | 5 | **Featured Properties** | Carousel or grid of curated listings | 60% | Optional — depends on having listings to feature |\n277: | 6 | **Value Props / Features** | Icon + text cards explaining platform benefits | 90% | Required |\n278: | 7 | **Trust / Social Proof** | Testimonials, press logos, review ratings, user counts | 80% | Recommended for credibility |\n279: | 8 | **Budget Calculator CTA** | \"How much rent can I afford?\" tool link | 40% | Differentiator opportunity |\n280: | 9 | **Mobile App Promotion** | App store badges, phone mockup, QR code | 50% | Optional (web-first) |\n281: | 10 | **For Property Managers** | CTA to list properties or advertise | 60% | Important if NestFind has property manager acquisition |\n282: | 11 | **Footer** | About, Contact, Terms, Privacy, Social links | 100% | Required |\n283: \n284: **Key Takeaway:** The hero + search bar is the single most important element. Every rental platform's landing page centers around the search input. Secondary sections build trust and explain value.\n285: \n286: ### Dashboard (Renter Hub)\n287: \n288: **Standard Elements (based on Zillow Renter Hub + design patterns):**\n289: \n290: | # | Element | Purpose | Prevalence |\n291: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n292: | 1 | **Saved Searches** | Quick access to active searches with new listing counts | 80% |\n293: | 2 | **Favorites Grid** | Preview of saved properties with quick remove | 70% |\n294: | 3 | **Messages/Inquiries Inbox** | List of sent inquiries with response statuses | 60% |\n295: | 4 | **Application Status** | Track submitted applications | 50% |\n296: | 5 | **Recommended Properties** | Algorithmic suggestions based on saved searches | 50% |\n297: \n298: **NestFind Renter Dashboard should include:** Saved Properties (favorites), Active Inquiries (sent messages), Saved Searches (optional), Account Settings link.\n299: \n300: ### Dashboard (Admin)\n301: \n302: **Standard Elements (based on Behance/Dribbble analysis):**\n303: \n304: | # | Element | Purpose | Prevalence |\n305: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n306: | 1 | **Stats Overview Cards** | Total Properties, Active/Archived, Total Inquiries, Total Users | 100% |\n307: | 2 | **Recent Inquiries** | Latest 5-10 inquiries with status badges and quick-view | 90% |\n308: | 3 | **Quick Actions** | \"Add Property\" button, \"View All Inquiries\" link | 80% |\n309: | 4 | **Properties Table** | Full CRUD list with search, filter, pagination | 100% |\n310: | 5 | **Property Create/Edit Form** | Multi-section form (photos, details, amenities, location) | 100% |\n311: | 6 | **Inquiries Table** | List with status filters (New, Read, Responded) | 100% |\n312: | 7 | **Inquiry Response View** | Message thread + reply form + status change | 80% |\n313: | 8 | **Users Table** | Renter list with status, activity, suspension toggle | 90% |\n314: | 9 | **Sidebar Navigation** | Collapsible sidebar with icons + labels | 100% |\n315: | 10 | **Top Bar** | Search, notifications, admin avatar dropdown | 90% |\n316: \n317: **Admin Dashboard Layout Convention:** Sidebar (200-250px) + Main Content Area. Stats cards in a horizontal row at top. Table or list below. \"Add New\" FAB or top-right button.\n318: \n319: ### Property Detail Page\n320: \n321: **Standard Sections (present in 90%+ of competitors):**\n322: \n323: | # | Section | Content | Prevalence |\n324: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n325: | 1 | **Photo Gallery** | Hero image + thumbnail strip + \"View all photos\" link | 100% |\n326: | 2 | **Header** | Title, address, price, bed/bath/sqft summary | 100% |\n327: | 3 | **Description** | Free-text property description paragraph(s) | 100% |\n328: | 4 | **Amenities Grid** | Icon + label grid (2-4 columns) | 95% |\n329: | 5 | **Floor Plan** | Floor plan image with zoom capability | 60% |\n330: | 6 | **Property Details/Specs** | Table: Type, Year Built, Deposit, Lease Terms, Pets, Parking | 80% |\n331: | 7 | **Location Map** | Embedded Google Map with pin | 95% |\n332: | 8 | **Inquiry/Contact** | Form (name, email, phone, message) + \"Send\" CTA | 100% |\n333: | 9 | **Favorite Toggle** | Heart icon for saving/unsaving | 90% |\n334: | 10 | **Similar/Related Properties** | Card row of suggested properties nearby | 50% |\n335: \n336: **Layout Convention:** Two-column layout — Main content (70%) left, Sidebar (30%) right. Sidebar is typically sticky and contains the inquiry form or contact CTA. On mobile, stacks to single column; inquiry CTA becomes a sticky bottom bar. Photo gallery always at top, full-width.\n337: \n338: ### Auth Pages (Login / Register)\n339: \n340: **Standard Patterns:**\n341: \n342: | # | Pattern | Details | Prevalence |\n343: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n344: | 1 | **Split-screen layout** | Left: brand/gradient, Right: form | 60% |\n345: | 2 | **Centered card layout** | Form in white card centered on colored background | 40% |\n346: | 3 | **Email + Password fields** | Full-width inputs, 48px height | 100% |\n347: | 4 | **Social login buttons** | Google, Apple, Facebook | 70% |\n348: | 5 | **\"Forgot Password\" link** | Below password field | 100% |\n349: | 6 | **\"Don't have an account? Sign up\"** | Below form | 100% |\n350: | 7 | **Password show/hide toggle** | Eye icon in password field right side | 70% |\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: ## PRD Reference Analysis\n355: \n356: | PRD Feature | Reference Source | Dominant UI Pattern | NestFind Implication |\n357: |-------------|-----------------|---------------------|---------------------|\n358: | Property search with filters | Zillow, Apartments.com | Map+list split, filter panel, property cards | Implement card+filter pattern; map is nice-to-have for v1 |\n359: | Property detail with photo gallery | Zillow, Airbnb | Full-width hero image, thumbnail strip, sectioned content below | Photo-first design; gallery with thumbnails |\n360: | Google Maps integration | Zillow, Apartments.com | Embedded map section with pin on detail page; optionally on search | Detail page map is mandatory |\n361: | Favorites / Save properties | Zillow, Airbnb | Heart icon toggle; dedicated Saved/Favorites page | Heart toggle on cards + detail page; Favorites page |\n362: | Inquiry / Contact form | Zillow, Apartments.com | Sidebar form or modal; name, email, phone, message + Send CTA | Sidebar on detail page; confirmation toast |\n363: | Admin property management | Dashboard patterns on Behance/Dribbble | Sidebar + table + multi-section form; stats cards | Follow standard admin dashboard layout |\n364: | Admin inquiry management | Apartments.com Manager, Behance | Table with status badges (New/Read/Responded), inline reply | Table with status filters, reply view |\n365: | Admin user management | Dashboard patterns | Table with status (Active/Suspended) + action buttons | Model after Stripe-style user tables |\n366: | Renter registration | Zillow, Airbnb | \"Join\" / \"Sign Up\" — email, name, password, optional phone | Simple form; social login optional for v1 |\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ## Design Gap Analysis\n371: \n372: **What competitors do well:**\n373: - Photo-first, immersive browsing experience\n374: - Map integration as core discovery mechanism\n375: - Robust, responsive filter panels\n376: - Trust-building elements (verified listings, reviews, badges)\n377: \n378: **What competitors do poorly (opportunity for NestFind):**\n379: - Ad-heavy interfaces that clutter the browsing experience\n380: - Overly complex filter panels that overwhelm casual renters\n381: - Slow page loads due to heavy tracking scripts\n382: - Poor mobile inquiry/applications flow\n383: \n384: **NestFind differentiators to emphasize in design:**\n385: 1. **Clean, ad-free browsing** — minimal, focused UI\n386: 2. **Streamlined inquiry flow** — simple contact form, no multi-step applications\n387: 3. **Quick favorites** — fast toggle without friction\n388: 4. **Simple admin dashboard** — focused on essential management tasks, not bloated with upsells\n389: 5. **Mobile-responsive as first principle** — not an afterthought\n390: \n391: ---\n392: \n393: *End of Domain Research. Proceed to Phase 3: Design Guide generation.*\n\n(End of file - total 393 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Domain Research — NestFind\n\n**Generated:** 2026-05-19\n**Source:** Phase 2.5 — Domain & Reference Research\n**Purpose:** Identify standard UI patterns and essential sections from top rental property listing platforms before Design Guide generation.\n\n---\n\n## Industry\n\n**Domain:** Real Estate / Rental Property Listings\n\nNestFind operates in the digital rental marketplace vertical — a subset of PropTech (Property Technology) focused exclusively on long-term residential rentals (as opposed to short-term/vacation rentals or property sales). The platform connects renters with available properties through search, discovery, detail views, favorites, and inquiry submission.\n\n**Market Context:**\n- The US online rental market is dominated by Zillow Rentals, Apartments.com, and Realtor.com Rentals\n- Mobile-first search behavior is standard — renters browse on mobile, apply on desktop\n- Key differentiator for newer entrants: streamlined UX, fewer ads, verified listings, built-in application/inquiry flows\n- Map-based search and card-based results are industry-standard UI patterns\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","time":{"start":1779181855462,"end":1779181855851}},"id":"prt_e3f809da1001oQlmKC2wHnwGiT","sessionID":"ses_1c07feae8ffe1KM7G6zC8Y3nGT","messageID":"msg_e3f808504001dLLLWwDeos3el0"}}
