{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779181983139,"sessionID":"ses_1c07feae8ffe1KM7G6zC8Y3nGT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_00_WqPWarSJOb6hEmDtPpeW6481","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","newString":"---\n\n### Competitor 3: Redfin Rentals (redfin.com/rentals)\n\n**Type:** Full real estate platform (sales + rentals), Redfin-owned\n**USP:** Operated by brokerage; unified renter/buyer/seller dashboard; \"Renter Dashboard\" for saved searches and application tracking\n\n**Live analysis (2026-05-19):**\n\n**Universal Gateway Approach:**\n- Redfin homepage serves Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, and Agent discovery under one roof\n- Primary nav: Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, Real Estate Agents — each with dropdown submenus\n- Hero section: \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with tabbed CTAs (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent)\n- Each CTA tab has its own visual, copy, and link\n\n**Rental-specific Navigation & Pages:**\n- Dedicated Rent top-nav dropdown with: Renter dashboard, Rental market tracker, \"How much rent can I afford?\", \"Should I rent or buy?\", Renter guide, \"List my home for rent\", \"Rental Tools dashboard\", \"US rental market trends\"\n- User dropdown (signed-in): Feed, Favorites & comments, Saved searches, My homes, Renter dashboard, My Redfin agent, Appointments, Open house schedule\n\n**Landing Page Sections (redfin.com):**\n1. **Hero + Tabs** — \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with 4 action cards (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent). Each has icon image + headline + description + CTA button.\n2. **App Download** — Phone mockup + QR code + \"Get the Redfin app\" with brief copy\n3. **Talk to a Redfin Agent** — \"Where are you searching for homes?\" input + assurance (\"no pressure or obligation\")\n4. **Latest Homes Grid** — City name grid cards: \"Browse the newest homes from around the country\" with ~20 city links\n5. **City/State Browse Links** — Alphabetical city links + state links for SEO and discovery\n6. **Footer** — 4-column structure: Join us (Agent, Referrals, Careers), Find homes faster (app badges), About us (Why Redfin, Community, Inclusion, Culture, Blog), Find us (Contact, Help), Subsidiaries (Rent., ApartmentGuide), Affiliated Business (Rocket Close, Rocket Mortgage)\n\n**Key Insights:**\n- Renter Dashboard is a first-class navigation item (not buried)\n- Financial tools are deeply integrated (rent affordability calculator, rent vs. buy calculator)\n- Strong cross-promotion with Redfin agent network and mortgage services\n- Desktop-first with prominent app download CTAs\n\n**Design Lessons for NestFind:**\n- Consider rent affordability calculator as a differentiator\n- Make \"Favorites\" a top-level nav item from the start\n- Rental-specific content (market trends, renter guides) drives SEO and engagement\n\n---","oldString":"---\n\n### Competitor 3: Airbnb (airbnb.com)"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md\n+++ /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md\n@@ -112,10 +112,46 @@\n - Property listing editor (photos, description, pricing, availability)\n \n ---\n \n-### Competitor 3: Airbnb (airbnb.com)\n+### Competitor 3: Redfin Rentals (redfin.com/rentals)\n \n+**Type:** Full real estate platform (sales + rentals), Redfin-owned\n+**USP:** Operated by brokerage; unified renter/buyer/seller dashboard; \"Renter Dashboard\" for saved searches and application tracking\n+\n+**Live analysis (2026-05-19):**\n+\n+**Universal Gateway Approach:**\n+- Redfin homepage serves Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, and Agent discovery under one roof\n+- Primary nav: Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, Real Estate Agents — each with dropdown submenus\n+- Hero section: \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with tabbed CTAs (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent)\n+- Each CTA tab has its own visual, copy, and link\n+\n+**Rental-specific Navigation & Pages:**\n+- Dedicated Rent top-nav dropdown with: Renter dashboard, Rental market tracker, \"How much rent can I afford?\", \"Should I rent or buy?\", Renter guide, \"List my home for rent\", \"Rental Tools dashboard\", \"US rental market trends\"\n+- User dropdown (signed-in): Feed, Favorites & comments, Saved searches, My homes, Renter dashboard, My Redfin agent, Appointments, Open house schedule\n+\n+**Landing Page Sections (redfin.com):**\n+1. **Hero + Tabs** — \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with 4 action cards (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent). Each has icon image + headline + description + CTA button.\n+2. **App Download** — Phone mockup + QR code + \"Get the Redfin app\" with brief copy\n+3. **Talk to a Redfin Agent** — \"Where are you searching for homes?\" input + assurance (\"no pressure or obligation\")\n+4. **Latest Homes Grid** — City name grid cards: \"Browse the newest homes from around the country\" with ~20 city links\n+5. **City/State Browse Links** — Alphabetical city links + state links for SEO and discovery\n+6. **Footer** — 4-column structure: Join us (Agent, Referrals, Careers), Find homes faster (app badges), About us (Why Redfin, Community, Inclusion, Culture, Blog), Find us (Contact, Help), Subsidiaries (Rent., ApartmentGuide), Affiliated Business (Rocket Close, Rocket Mortgage)\n+\n+**Key Insights:**\n+- Renter Dashboard is a first-class navigation item (not buried)\n+- Financial tools are deeply integrated (rent affordability calculator, rent vs. buy calculator)\n+- Strong cross-promotion with Redfin agent network and mortgage services\n+- Desktop-first with prominent app download CTAs\n+\n+**Design Lessons for NestFind:**\n+- Consider rent affordability calculator as a differentiator\n+- Make \"Favorites\" a top-level nav item from the start\n+- Rental-specific content (market trends, renter guides) drives SEO and engagement\n+\n+---\n+\n **Type:** Short-term rental marketplace\n **USP:** Best-in-class UX, immersive design, host/guest marketplace\n \n **Landing Page Patterns:**\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","patch":"Index: /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md\n+++ /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md\n@@ -112,10 +112,46 @@\n - Property listing editor (photos, description, pricing, availability)\n \n ---\n \n-### Competitor 3: Airbnb (airbnb.com)\n+### Competitor 3: Redfin Rentals (redfin.com/rentals)\n \n+**Type:** Full real estate platform (sales + rentals), Redfin-owned\n+**USP:** Operated by brokerage; unified renter/buyer/seller dashboard; \"Renter Dashboard\" for saved searches and application tracking\n+\n+**Live analysis (2026-05-19):**\n+\n+**Universal Gateway Approach:**\n+- Redfin homepage serves Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, and Agent discovery under one roof\n+- Primary nav: Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, Real Estate Agents — each with dropdown submenus\n+- Hero section: \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with tabbed CTAs (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent)\n+- Each CTA tab has its own visual, copy, and link\n+\n+**Rental-specific Navigation & Pages:**\n+- Dedicated Rent top-nav dropdown with: Renter dashboard, Rental market tracker, \"How much rent can I afford?\", \"Should I rent or buy?\", Renter guide, \"List my home for rent\", \"Rental Tools dashboard\", \"US rental market trends\"\n+- User dropdown (signed-in): Feed, Favorites & comments, Saved searches, My homes, Renter dashboard, My Redfin agent, Appointments, Open house schedule\n+\n+**Landing Page Sections (redfin.com):**\n+1. **Hero + Tabs** — \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with 4 action cards (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent). Each has icon image + headline + description + CTA button.\n+2. **App Download** — Phone mockup + QR code + \"Get the Redfin app\" with brief copy\n+3. **Talk to a Redfin Agent** — \"Where are you searching for homes?\" input + assurance (\"no pressure or obligation\")\n+4. **Latest Homes Grid** — City name grid cards: \"Browse the newest homes from around the country\" with ~20 city links\n+5. **City/State Browse Links** — Alphabetical city links + state links for SEO and discovery\n+6. **Footer** — 4-column structure: Join us (Agent, Referrals, Careers), Find homes faster (app badges), About us (Why Redfin, Community, Inclusion, Culture, Blog), Find us (Contact, Help), Subsidiaries (Rent., ApartmentGuide), Affiliated Business (Rocket Close, Rocket Mortgage)\n+\n+**Key Insights:**\n+- Renter Dashboard is a first-class navigation item (not buried)\n+- Financial tools are deeply integrated (rent affordability calculator, rent vs. buy calculator)\n+- Strong cross-promotion with Redfin agent network and mortgage services\n+- Desktop-first with prominent app download CTAs\n+\n+**Design Lessons for NestFind:**\n+- Consider rent affordability calculator as a differentiator\n+- Make \"Favorites\" a top-level nav item from the start\n+- Rental-specific content (market trends, renter guides) drives SEO and engagement\n+\n+---\n+\n **Type:** Short-term rental marketplace\n **USP:** Best-in-class UX, immersive design, host/guest marketplace\n \n **Landing Page Patterns:**\n","additions":37,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","time":{"start":1779181982847,"end":1779181983137}},"id":"prt_e3f822fa9001JAcH3MkXskLwpv","sessionID":"ses_1c07fe